      <p class="facing-card-body">Caused by prolonged tension on the hair follicle — from tight braids, ponytails, weaves, and extensions worn repeatedly over time. The hairline, temples, and edges are typically most affected. Caught early enough, the follicles can often recover. The Crown Restoration Program prioritizes protective, low-tension installation methods that allow the scalp to breathe and the follicle to rest while the hair is still covered and styled.</p>
